 <h2><u>Bangle of Disease</u></h2><br><br>This quest results in this bracer:<br><br><img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/danapics/BangleofDiseaseWarding.gif"><br><br><br>Ok, so its not fantastic, but the effect is an instaclick (click from inventory) <b>40 Disease Resist</b> that you can cast on others. Making it a severely useful item!<br><br>That means that one person could potentially keep a group in instaclickies, and give an entire raid +40 DR.<br><br><br>Whats more, the item acts as a key to the <a href="zones.php3?zone=decay">Crypt of Decay</a> for those without the flag. Sounds good right? Now all you need to do is get it.<br><br><br>To get it, you need to loot the flesh of the following four named flys: <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11642">A Generian Larva</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11084">A Harrior Larva</a>, <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=12974">A Scaevian Larva</a> and <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10383">A Sengian Larva</a>. These are rare spawns, and will occasionally spawn in place of the similarily named "larvae" (the named are "larva"). So kill the placeholders until you get the mob you need. Something worth thinking about when <a href='index2.php3?page=podh'>Soloing the Plane of Disease</a>.<br><br>Once you have the four flesh, hand them in to a wandering Ogre named <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10448">Grimror Plaguebringer</a> to get your bracer.<br><br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br>Zonelookup Failed!